The son of Adebayo Alao-Akala, a former governor of Oyo State, Olamijuwonlo Ayodeji Alao-Akala, has joined other well-wishers to congratulate Mr. Sunday Dare on his appointment as a minister of Youths and Sports by President Muhammadu Buhari. Olamijuwonlo, who expressed confidence in his ability to carry out the assignment well and make their party, the All Progressives Congress (APC) proud lauded President Muhammadu Buhari for making a good choice. Buhari approves Ipaye’s re-appointment, others in VP’s… Gov race:PDP clears 34 aspirants for Kogi, Bayelsa primaries Sonaiya applauds Sanwo-Olu for 32% female cabinet, urges… Joint military exercise shut down activities at Nigerian… ALSO READ: Aregbesola assumes duty, talks tough on internal security challenge He described the appointment as one that will be in the interest of Oyo State, adding that, “I join the great people of Oyo State and other well-wishers across the globe to congratulate you on your inauguration by President Muhammadu Buhari as the Minister of Youths and Sports of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. “Your appointment will give birth to positive changes to the lives of our unemployed youths, industrious youths as well as talented sportsmen and sportswomen. Congratulations on your appointment and wish you every success in your new duties,” he stated. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
